airdropMint(address,bytes32,bytes).details: REMOVED staking logic - Registry handles all financial operations      MySBT only mints the SBT token itself      Called by Registry.safeMintForRole() for admin airdrops

returns.isNew: True if new SBT was minted

mintForRole(address,bytes32,bytes).details: Called by Registry when user registers a role via registerRole()      - Creates new SBT if user doesn't have one      - Records role metadata on existing SBT      - No staking/burning here (Registry handles that)

returns.isNewMint: True if new SBT was minted

paused().details: Returns true if the contract is paused, and false otherwise.
